"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-27-celine-dion-performs-at-2024-paris-olympics-amid-health-battle-video\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Famous Canadian singer, Celine Dion, Friday, performed at the opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympics in Paris.  This was Celine's first live performance in 4 years, following her battle with stiff person syndrome, SPS, a rare neurological disorder.  At the ceremony, she delivered a performance of Edith Piaf's 1950 song 'Hymne \\u00e0 l'amour' to close the ceremony at the Eiffel Tower.  DAILY POST reports that the 56-year-old singercharged $2 million for the 2024 Olympics performance.  This was Dion's second performance at the Olympic Games, having performed 'The Power of the Dream' in 1996 in Atlanta.  Celine Dion#Paris2024#Olympics#Olympic2024pic.twitter.com/3f8Pm0qqrE  - Celine Dion Icon (@celinedionlcon)July 26, 2024    1996 performance  Atlanta 1996 Paris 2024  C\\u00e9line Dionpic.twitter.com/PHnt4JOUUd  - The Olympic Games (@Olympics)July 26, 2024    'It's gift I will never forget' - Lady Gaga relishes performance at Paris Olympics opening ceremony  I have never said I love you to anyone before - Falz  I do not know Celine Dion - Arsenal star, Bukayo Saka  Nigeria loses out on all medals as 2024 Paris Olympics ends  US Election: I did not permit Trump to use my song for his campaign - Celine Dion clarifies  'I will be remembered for my classics even if I stop singing' - Celine Dion  2024 Paris Olympics: Nigerian sprinter, Favour Ofili denied 100m spot  Beyonc\\u00e9 introduces Team USA at 2024 Paris Olympics  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"